Three of the four police officers accused of killing Mthokozisi Ntumba have had previousÂ  brushes with the law, including attempted murder and drunken driving. Sowetan has established that the three Public Order Policing (POP) unit officers, Cidrass Motseothata, 43, Madimetsa Legodi, 37, and Victor Mohammed, 51, have had run-ins with the law and some of their cases date back to 2008. The fourth officer Tshepiso Kekana has no past criminal cases or any that are pending. Motseothata, Legodi, Mohammed and Kekana are in custody for allegedly killing Ntumba, who was shot with rubber bullets during a student protest in Braamfontein, Johannesburg, on March 10. For more on this article, please visit SowetanLIVE.